text: Robert Frost (1874–1963) was an American poet. Robert Frost may also refer to: *Robert Frost (cricketer) (1793–?), English cricketer *Robert I. Frost (born c. 1960), British historian *Rob Frost (1950–2007), English Christian evangelist, broadcaster and author *Bob Frost, 2008 Rolex Sports Car Series season *Robert Frost (pioneer), one of the dead in the Fort Parker massacre *Robert S. Frost (1942–2013), American composer and music educator ==See also== * *Robert Frost Middle School (disambiguation)
